        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 20 at 3:13PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 313 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles southeast of Downtown Asheville, or near Skyland, moving south
at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Downtown Asheville, East Asheville, Arden, Fletcher, Fairview In
Buncombe County, Biltmore Forest, Asheville Airport, Skyland, B.R.
Parkway-Nc Arboretum To East Asheville, and Avery Creek.
</description>
        <instruction>Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
